    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001749_0001" n="0001"/>

<lb/>
<lb/><opener><space extent="2" unit="words"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U">32 <space extent="4" unit="words"/>55</add>
<lb/><dateline><space extent="2" unit="words"/><placeName>Shupanga</placeName> <date when="1862-03-15">15<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> March
<lb/><space extent="5" unit="words"/>1862</date></dateline>
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Rowley</persName></salute></opener>
<lb/><p>This is a terrible
<lb/>blow to the mission &amp;
<lb/>makes me very much
<lb/>depressed in view
<lb/>of the effect it will
<lb/>have on all our
<lb/>efforts - However we
<lb/>must not swerve
<lb/>from the work we
<lb/>have undertaken
<lb/>come what will and 
<lb/>I trust you will all
<lb/>feel the importance</p>

<lb/><cb rend="vertical"/><!--This vertical text connected to end of letter-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">In January - She is much too deep &amp; long
<lb/>Excuse this hasty note we are starting</p>

	<pb facs="liv_001749_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">of sticking more closely<!--paragraph here to validate. EC-->
<lb/>together and supporting
<lb/>each other than ever - 
<lb/>Remember pray that
<lb/>the eyes of the most
<lb/>influential people in
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="country">England</settlement></placeName> are upon you 
<lb/>and should anything
<lb/>present you doing
<lb/>your duty manfully
<lb/>you will be set down
<lb/>as a parcel of canting
<lb/>hypocrites that ought 
<lb/>never to have been <w>en-
<lb break="no"/>trusted</w> with anything
<lb/>Let every little difference
<lb/>dwindle into insignificance
<lb/>before the great work</p>
<lb/><cb rend="vertical"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">for the sea hoping this may find you</p>

	<pb facs="liv_001749_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="6" unit="words"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U">56</add>
<lb/>in which you are engaged
<lb/>Excuse my saying so 
<lb/>much in the <unclear cert="medium">hortatory</unclear>
<lb/>style -</p>
<lb/><p>We could not carry up 
<lb/>35 tons of the new steamer
<lb/>took 3 weeks to come
<lb/>up to <placeName><settlement type="village">Shupanga</settlement></placeName> - <w>un<supplied>-</supplied> 
<lb break="no"/>loaded</w> 5 tons there - tried
<lb/>again and were forced 
<lb/>to unload all - put her
<lb/>together and tow her up
<lb/>in <date when="1862-05">May</date> next - you
<lb/>will see how entirely
<lb/>it is out of our power
<lb/>to serve you with this
<lb/>steamer as I would - 
<lb/>We are entirely out of
<lb/>provisions - and have 
<lb/>no prospect of getting</p>
<lb/><cb rend="vertical"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">in health &amp; good spirits <space extent="1" unit="words"/>I am the
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>


	<pb facs="liv_001749_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">any except by going to
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName><!-- unsure if this is a city. --> - and should
<lb/>we be too late for the
<lb/>ascent of the <placeName><geogName type="river">Shire</geogName></placeName> will
<lb/>lose a season - Then
<lb/>the <term type="occupation">bishop</term> came down
<lb/>in <date when="1861-11"><choice><abbr>Nov<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>November</expan></choice></date> he wished to go
<lb/>down to the <placeName>Ruo</placeName> &amp; explore
<lb/>upwards but I objected
<lb/>very strongly as the <seg type="weather">rains</seg>
<lb/>fell every afternoon and
<lb/>would knock him up -
<lb/>Well we went down one day
<lb/>and then were detained over
<lb/>6 weeks with a large marsh
<lb/>on each side of us &amp; lost
<lb/>our first man in the
<lb/><orgName>Expedition</orgName> - we stood two
<lb/>days <measure>1 mile above</measure> <placeName>Ruo</placeName> but 
<lb/>on <date when="1861-01-01">1<hi rend="sup underline">st</hi> January </date> no <term type="occupation">bishop</term>
<lb/>could be heard of - We did
<lb/>not reach the sea till late <!--Livingstone continues this on the first page in vertical text--></p>
            </div>
